  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Score the pork belly into diamond shapes, cutting about 1/4 inch deep.",
    "In a small bowl, mix together hojicha-infused oil, cane sugar, light soy sauce, and rice vinegar to make the glaze.",
    "Brush the glaze over the scored pork belly, making sure to get some into the scored lines.",
    "Place the pork belly on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper and bake for 20 minutes, or until caramelized.",
    "While the pork belly is baking, steam the bao dough according to package instructions, or until soft and fluffy.",
    "Assemble the baos by placing a piece of boiled bao dough into a bamboo steamer basket, then topping with a piece of the glazed pork belly, and finally drizzling with hojicha-infused oil.",
    "Garnish with scallions and sesame seeds, if desired."
  ],
